Author: Cryptocracyforall
Title: [ANN] ZETOCHAIN-pioneering a scalable, global supply chain powered by Blockchain
Body: The benefit seems most tangible for the consumer. If a product has been shipped and was outside the temperature threshold but doesn't visibly look spoiled, is it destroyed?

Author: zetochain
Title: [ANN] ZETOCHAIN-pioneering a scalable, global supply chain powered by Blockchain
Body: Yes, it should be. Often these issues are not discovered which can lead to food poisoning or worse. By continuously monitoring the product and environment, and alerting participants to issues before they happen we hope to reduce the food that needs to be destroyed. But, if a food product becomes unsafe, we will capture that and alert the owner that it needs to be destroyed.

Author: zetoteam
Title: [ANN] ZETOCHAIN-pioneering a scalable, global supply chain powered by Blockchain
Body: Thanks for the questions.  In terms of competitors: Our main competitor would be someone like Ambrosus.  The key for us is that ZetoChain is being brought to market by a team that has previously developed and delivered a market leading solution. We're building on top of our existing IoT platform and our existing customers are poised to trial and deploy the solution as soon as it is ready. The cold chain for the global retail market is a complicated industry that Zeto has deep expertise and experience in.  I'm not sure that I understand your question about the token. Could you elaborate just a bit?  Thanks.

Author: zetochain
Title: [ANN] ZETOCHAIN-pioneering a scalable, global supply chain powered by Blockchain
Body: Don't apologise, all great questions!   I notice that Walmart and IBM are trying something like this and that's what caught my eye with this. What makes you think you can be competitive with them?  Correct, Walmart are investigating this area, so too are Carrefour and many other of the worlds largest retailers. Walmarts solution will be for Walmart only, we differ in that, like our current IoT platform, we will build a product available to any retailer and retail group such as our existing customers. We will not be directly competing with them as they will not be selling their product to their competitors. They also will not make the information available to consumers and they don't monitor environmental data (temperature etc.) in real time.   What exactly is zetochain?  ZetoChain is a blockchain solution to ensure food safety from farm to fork. It will track traceability information and environmental data (temperature, humidity etc.) as product moves from the factory all the way to a store. When you scan the ZetoLabel with your phone, you can see when the item was packed, what temperatures it was stored at etc. and be confident that what you are purchasing is safe and fresh.  An example of one benefit to the cold chain is a reduction in stock loss. Because we are building it on our existing market leading IoT platform, a truck driver can get an SMS informing them their door isn't properly secured, a warehouse manager can get a phone call in the middle of the night telling them their freezer room has lost power, a retailer can get an email informing them a freezer is in need of maintenance etc.  So customers can verify their food is safe, and everyone in the cold chain saves money.

Author: zetochain
Title: [ANN] ZETOCHAIN-pioneering a scalable, global supply chain powered by Blockchain
Body: We will not force any of our existing customers to switch. We have spoken to a number of them about the project and all were excited and saw its huge potential. Switching is something we believe will happen organically.

Author: zetochain
Title: [ANN] ZETOCHAIN-pioneering a scalable, global supply chain powered by Blockchain
Body: Thanks!   Will you all disclose what partnerships you have during the sale?  We've seen teams like to make announcements about making announcements that turn out to be duds.  Zeto could set itself apart from the rest by being specific up front.     We have a number of partnerships secured, and we will announce their names in time.  We also have a number of exciting partners and customers working with us, but as they are large organisations all public announcements need to go through their communications departments. We are working through that process with them now.   I see you are going with ERC20 tokens.  Has the team considered any other token types like NEP-5 for example?  We have looked at NEO and it is a very exciting project, however for the public token we felt ERC-20 is the one most people are comfortable with, most wallets support etc.

Author: MadWun
Title: [ANN] ZETOCHAIN-pioneering a scalable, global supply chain powered by Blockchain
Body: I like them both but Ethereum's scalability issues scare me sometimes.  I missed out on an ICO in October because of the Crypto Kitty fiasco.  Only glaring advantage on the surface I see is NEO's 10,000 transactions per second vs ETH's 15 yet ETH has the name recognition and tons of projects already on the market so it comes down to personal preference.
